section.section:
Untested blood may be transfused only in an emergency situation in which the attending physician determines a patient is in imminent danger of death or serious physical injury and no tested and labeled blood as set forth under KRS 214.458 is readily available to alleviate the emergency situation; provided, however, that the attending physician shall obtain specific prior consent for the transfusion from the patient in the emergency situation or if the patient's condition renders the patient incapable of giving consent, seek from the next of kin of the patient, if available, prior informed consent to transfuse any untested blood. For purposes of this section, the patient's "next of kin" means, in the following order;
The spouse of the patient;
If there is none, then the mother or father of the patient;
If there is none, then any adult son or daughter of the patient; or
If there is none, then any brother or sister of the patient.
